# Svelte Rules

## Components
- Keep components focused and small
- Use TypeScript with lang="ts" in script blocks
- Use $props() for component inputs (Svelte 5 runes)
- Use $state() for reactive state declarations

## Reactivity (Svelte 5)
- Use $state() for reactive variables
- Use $derived() for computed values
- Use $effect() sparingly — prefer derived state
- Use $bindable() for two-way binding props

## Patterns
- Use {#snippet} for reusable template blocks
- Use {#each} with keyed items for lists
- Use {#await} for promise handling in templates
- Use actions (use:action) for DOM behavior

## State Management
- Use Svelte stores for shared state
- Use context API (setContext/getContext) for component tree state
- Keep stores simple — derive complex state with computed

## Styling
- Use scoped styles (default in Svelte)
- Use CSS custom properties for theming
- Use class: directive for conditional classes
